<div dir="ltr">Dear Friends,<br><br>A year on from the launch of the<a href="https://ict4peace.crowdmap.com/" target="_blank"> ICT in Conflict &amp; Disaster Response and Peacebuilding Crowdmap</a> and we now have over 800 
entries on our map and the number is growing continually.  If you are not regularly using this resource for 
networking and collaboration I encourage you to look again and find out 
who&#39;s doing what in your area, country and around the world.  Have you 
thought about how you might use the information held on this 
map?  You could check out local initiatives in your area,  research projects in
 another country, or see what you 
can learn from another organisation working on a similar theme.<br><br>To
 mark our 1 year anniversary we are sending around a brief survey to 
assess the needs of our users.  We would appreciate if you could take <b>two minutes</b> to answer <a href="http://ictinemergency.polldaddy.com/s/new-survey" target="_blank">10 very simple questions</a>
 about this crowdmap.  Finding out your needs helps us to better improve
 the service and to move forward in the project.  We are keen to learn 
how you use this map: <a href="http://ictinemergency.polldaddy.com/s/new-survey" target="_blank">http://ictinemergency.<u></u>polldaddy.com/s/new-survey</a><br><br>We look forward to your feedback and to seeing any new projects, programmes or initiatives you add to the map!<br>


<br>Best wishes &amp; happy mapping,<br><br>Christine Broenner &amp; Laura Morris<div><div><img src="https://mail.google.com/mail/images/cleardot.gif"><br><span><font color="#888888">ICT in Conflict &amp; Disaster Response and Peacebuilding Crowdmap<br>

